My Authority on boats is derived directly from ignorance and floating (motoring) down the river on low water.  <br>
I tore up two motors the first year and put a hole in one boat.  Only tore up one motor the second year.  We won't talk about my falling out of the boat while hitting ledge rock sideways with a full 2 g's of force.  (Can throw ya pretty good).  Ouch!!!!  Fills up the waders too!<br>
<br>
My motivation is I can't get my feet wet.  I get a bad rash and it hurts like Heck.  <br>
<br>
So I learned to go down the river from Rivercliff to Crooked Creek which is about 20 miles or so .(past shoestring actually).<br>
<br>
I am not an expert on boats but I do spend about 240 days a year in one and have done so for the last 8 years.<br>
It will be nine this november.  <br>
<br>
What I am an expert in is riding the rise or staying in front of the rise.  Of 100 guides or so on the upper end of the river (ie Dam to Crooked Creek) about 20 miles there are only three or four that can do it with a fly rod and one needs a good boat to do this with or a heck of a lot of skill. <br>
<br>
<br>
Ride the rise.......<br>
best fishing there is.......<br>
<br>
Jimmy T.<br>
